  "text": "Moreover, in the existing photovoltaic power generation system, several PV modules are usually connected in series-parallel for the sake of getting higher voltage and power levels, and then output power through a larger capacity inverter. However, it is difficult to ensure that they are all working at the maximum power point due to the characteristic difference among PV modules, which causes power loss. In recent years, scholars present the concept of micro-inverter that is suitable for single PV module, and could dramatically improve the efficiency of power generation because it is able to ensure each module is working at maximum power point [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] .",
